cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper focuses on event recognition in still images using deep learning methods, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The use of deep learning methods also suggests that cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely sub-categories. The paper also explores different scenarios for utilizing OS-CNNs, which involves transfer learning, indicating that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image classification, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
